track.name: Pretty Thing
comments: Bo Diddley and Chuck Berry laid down every guitar riff used by Rock bands from 1956 to 1971.
The guitar sound or tone throughout the Rolling Stone's song "Please Don't Go" sounds a lot like this, 12 years later.
I went into the record shop in 1963  in the UK to buy "Memphis Tennessee"/"Let It Rock" by Chuck Berry but came out with this great Bo Diddley song.
